column133: In the past 12 months: - I find that when I start eating certain foods, I end up eating much more than planned.
column134: In the past 12 months: - I find myself continuing to consume certain foods even though I am no longer hungry.
column135: In the past 12 months: - I eat to the point where I feel physically ill.
column136: In the past 12 months: - Not eating certain types of food or cutting down on certain types of food is something I worry about.
column137: In the past 12 months: - I spend a lot of time feeling sluggish or fatigued from overeating.
column138: In the past 12 months: - I find myself constantly eating certain foods throughout the day.
column139: In the past 12 months: - I find that when certain foods are not available, I will go out of my way to obtain them. For example, I will drive to the store to purchase certain foods even though I have other options available to me at home.
column140: In the past 12 months: - There have been times when I consumed certain foods so often or in such large quantities that I started to eat food instead of working, spending time with my family or friends, or engaging in other important activities or recreational activities I enjoy.
